vblade: vblade (Virtual EtherDriveÂ® blade AoE target)
vblade:
vblade: The vblade is the virtual EtherDrive (R) blade, a program that makes a
vblade: seekable file available over an ethernet local area network (LAN) via
vblade: the ATA over Ethernet (AoE) protocol.
vblade: The seekable file is typically a block device like /dev/md0 but even
vblade: regular files will work.  Sparse files can be especially convenient.
vblade: When vblade exports the block storage over AoE it becomes a storage
vblade: target.  Another host on the same LAN can access the storage if it has
vblade: a compatible aoe kernel driver.
vblade:
